01:14:29.424 --> 01:14:30.968
MAN: As I was saying,
our residential department...

01:14:31.051 --> 01:14:32.219
How are the kids?

01:14:32.344 --> 01:14:34.721
MAN:...consumers
reacted to our packages...

01:14:34.805 --> 01:14:36.473
Mark Baum really did that.

01:14:36.557 --> 01:14:37.808
When we were in Vegas, he did that.

01:14:37.891 --> 01:14:40.060
He said that, he took the call.

01:14:40.519 --> 01:14:42.229
Now you see what I had to deal with?

01:14:42.563 --> 01:14:44.439
(GUNFIRE)

01:14:51.029 --> 01:14:52.573
(SHOUTING)

01:14:53.073 --> 01:14:54.575
(WHOOPING)

01:14:55.909 --> 01:14:58.036
Yeah, the Beretta... Meh.

01:14:58.120 --> 01:15:00.330
But this Uzi is fucking awesome!

01:15:00.414 --> 01:15:03.000
I need this CDO machine
to run for another two years.

01:15:03.083 --> 01:15:06.336
And then I'm rich as fuck
and I got my house in Aspen.

01:15:06.420 --> 01:15:09.631
But do you have any concerns
about the performance

01:15:09.715 --> 01:15:11.300
of the underlying securitizations?

01:15:11.383 --> 01:15:13.177
It's easy to see that delinquencies

01:15:13.260 --> 01:15:16.138
and default rates
are on the rise right now.

01:15:16.221 --> 01:15:18.390
Could you please stop
being such a buzzkill, dude?

01:15:18.765 --> 01:15:21.310
We didn't bring you out here
to talk about work, bro.

01:15:21.393 --> 01:15:22.853
Why did you bring us out here?

01:15:22.936 --> 01:15:26.148
Because we need to be able
to expense the ammo to a client.

01:15:26.231 --> 01:15:29.234
I'm gonna go shoot some terrorists.
Watch how it's done, boys!

01:15:29.443 --> 01:15:30.694
CHARLIE: These guys are morons.

01:15:30.819 --> 01:15:32.446
- Fucking tool.
- MAN: Whoo!

01:15:32.779 --> 01:15:33.822
These guys are morons.

01:15:34.948 --> 01:15:36.116
Fuck, yes! Boom!

01:15:36.283 --> 01:15:37.409
Yeah, man!

01:15:37.492 --> 01:15:39.870
We need to be buying up every swap
we can get our hands on here.

01:15:39.953 --> 01:15:42.247
Just hold on, okay? Hold on.

01:15:42.331 --> 01:15:44.625
My brother's ex-girlfriend
works for the SEC.

01:15:44.750 --> 01:15:46.585
She just told me she's in town, okay?

01:15:46.668 --> 01:15:48.795
So, if we're missing something,
maybe she can tell me.

01:15:48.921 --> 01:15:50.547
You know, give me some insight.

01:15:50.631 --> 01:15:52.382
In the meantime, you go to the main floor

01:15:52.466 --> 01:15:54.176
<i>and price some swaps.</i>

01:15:54.635 --> 01:15:56.053
JAMIE: (STAMMERS)
Well, actually, we're

01:15:56.136 --> 01:15:58.639
about to invest in housing bonds, and...

01:15:58.722 --> 01:16:01.391
I was wondering if the SEC
is worried about them at all.

01:16:01.475 --> 01:16:04.228
I know you're not allowed
to tell me specifics, but just generally.

01:16:04.311 --> 01:16:06.521
Oh, we don't
investigate mortgage bonds.

01:16:06.605 --> 01:16:09.942
Truth is, since we got our budget cut,
we don't investigate much.

01:16:11.985 --> 01:16:14.947
- Then why are you here? I thought...
- I'm not here for the SEC.

01:16:15.030 --> 01:16:16.698
I'm here on my own dime.

01:16:17.658 --> 01:16:20.869
I'm floating my resume
to some big banks.

01:16:20.953 --> 01:16:22.537
How's your brother, by the way?

01:16:22.621 --> 01:16:24.498
How are you floating
your resume to big banks?

01:16:24.581 --> 01:16:25.958
I mean, you're supposed to be the ones,

01:16:26.083 --> 01:16:27.417
you know, policing the big banks.

01:16:27.501 --> 01:16:28.919
Grow up, Jamie.

01:16:29.002 --> 01:16:32.756
There must be some kind of law against
working for a financial institution

01:16:32.839 --> 01:16:36.051
right after you've been working
in financial regulation, right?

01:16:36.134 --> 01:16:38.220
No. No.

01:16:39.304 --> 01:16:41.848
(GASPS) Hey! Dougie!

01:16:42.683 --> 01:16:45.644
Hey! Come over here.
What are you doing at Caesars?

01:16:45.727 --> 01:16:47.229
He's at Goldman.

01:16:47.854 --> 01:16:48.897
See you.

01:16:48.981 --> 01:16:54.027
We can do BBB-level swaps
at 500 basis points. Maybe.

01:16:54.111 --> 01:16:57.906
You're pricing the swaps
like the bond is gonna collapse

01:16:57.990 --> 01:17:00.367
even though the bond value's
going up? Really?

01:17:00.909 --> 01:17:01.994
Sign of the times.

01:17:02.077 --> 01:17:03.437
CHARLIE: What the hell
is going on?

01:18:01.970 --> 01:18:05.766
Lewis, can you come in
early tomorrow, please?

01:18:05.849 --> 01:18:08.143
I need to unload the AIG
and Countrywide

01:18:08.226 --> 01:18:09.686
and Freddie Mac positions

01:18:09.770 --> 01:18:12.272
so that we can afford
the premiums on the...

01:18:12.439 --> 01:18:13.440
(SIGHS)

01:18:13.523 --> 01:18:16.443
...core mortgage shorts on the swaps.

01:18:16.902 --> 01:18:18.403
No problem, Dr. Burry.

01:18:20.447 --> 01:18:21.615
- Dr. Burry?
- Hmm?

01:18:23.533 --> 01:18:24.534
(CLEARS THROAT)

01:18:25.202 --> 01:18:26.244
If the investors withdraw,

01:18:26.328 --> 01:18:29.081
what's going to happen here?
Are we done?

01:18:29.206 --> 01:18:31.124
Honestly, I don't know.

01:18:35.379 --> 01:18:37.089
(STAMMERS)

01:18:38.799 --> 01:18:41.051
The bonds aren't going down.

01:18:42.302 --> 01:18:44.971
They won't move. It's possible

01:18:45.389 --> 01:18:49.976
that we are in a completely
fraudulent system.

01:18:51.395 --> 01:18:54.064
Or... (STAMMERS) You're wrong.

01:18:58.819 --> 01:18:59.903
Sure.

01:19:00.654 --> 01:19:04.658
It's possible I'm wrong.
I just don't know how.

01:19:09.371 --> 01:19:13.542
I guess when someone's wrong,
they never...

01:19:13.917 --> 01:19:16.169
They never know how.

01:19:20.465 --> 01:19:21.508
LEWIS: See you in the morning.

01:19:21.633 --> 01:19:22.676
Yeah.

01:19:24.469 --> 01:19:26.471
Even Bear upped their prices.

01:19:27.055 --> 01:19:29.558
And they keep calling us Brownhole.

01:19:29.641 --> 01:19:31.268
You just don't have the money
or the reputation.

01:19:31.351 --> 01:19:32.686
Don't take it personally.

01:19:32.811 --> 01:19:34.104
I don't think I have
the strip club in me tonight.

01:19:34.187 --> 01:19:37.858
I'm just gonna get some ginger ale
and watch some pay-per-view.

01:19:37.941 --> 01:19:40.318
I'll book us some flights out
for the morning.

01:19:41.736 --> 01:19:44.364
CHARLIE: (STAMMERS) A deal.
We need a deal, right? A deal.

01:19:44.448 --> 01:19:46.241
We need a deal we can afford.

01:19:46.366 --> 01:19:48.660
We need a deal
that they're not gonna refuse.

01:19:48.743 --> 01:19:52.080
So... What can we do? We can...

01:19:53.373 --> 01:19:56.293
The AA tranches. What if we
bet against the AA tranches?

01:19:56.376 --> 01:19:57.711
Who's not gonna take that bet?

01:19:58.420 --> 01:20:01.339
We know they say
they're 95% AAA-rated,

01:20:01.423 --> 01:20:03.425
but in reality they're more like 25%.

01:20:03.508 --> 01:20:05.927
Some of them are 0%!

01:20:06.011 --> 01:20:08.638
We also know that if
the bottom tranches fail at over 8%,

01:20:08.722 --> 01:20:09.890
the upper tranches are affected.

01:20:09.973 --> 01:20:11.183
They go to zero.

01:20:11.433 --> 01:20:14.394
I'll bet you right now
that those AA's are actually like B's.

01:20:14.853 --> 01:20:17.939
I rarely ever say these words,
but I think Charlie's right.

01:20:18.273 --> 01:20:19.941
Look, Ben.

01:20:21.610 --> 01:20:23.028
The payoff

01:20:23.528 --> 01:20:24.946
is 200 to 1.

01:20:25.030 --> 01:20:27.073
But they're all taking
the ratings at face value.

01:20:27.199 --> 01:20:30.577
So they're charging pennies
on the dollar a bet against the AA's.

01:20:32.204 --> 01:20:35.040
Just when I start thinking
you guys are clowns...

01:20:35.123 --> 01:20:37.626
No one on the planet's
betting against AA's.

01:20:37.709 --> 01:20:40.629
The banks will think we're either high
or having a stroke.

01:20:40.712 --> 01:20:43.048
They'll take every dime we have to offer.

01:20:45.634 --> 01:20:46.968
Kinda brilliant.

01:20:48.762 --> 01:20:50.847
This is what we did
that no one else thought of.

01:20:50.931 --> 01:20:53.850
Not even Baum or Burry
thought to short the AA's.

01:20:53.934 --> 01:20:55.310
But we did.

01:20:55.393 --> 01:20:56.937
Little Brownhole Capital.

01:20:57.270 --> 01:21:02.192
We're interested in shorting
some of the AA tranche of CDOs.

01:21:02.275 --> 01:21:04.069
Come on, guys, what's the angle?

01:21:04.152 --> 01:21:06.446
Oh, got no angle.
We're new to this. We're just excited.

01:21:06.571 --> 01:21:10.283
We want to do $15 million
in swaps on the AA tranche.

01:21:10.742 --> 01:21:11.826
I don't understand.

01:21:11.910 --> 01:21:14.538
You can buy as much
AA tranche as you want.

01:21:16.748 --> 01:21:18.875
$40 million against the AA.

01:21:18.959 --> 01:21:21.169
Brother, I will sell you
as much as you want.

01:21:21.461 --> 01:21:23.672
You understand perfectly, Bob.
You want the deal?

01:21:24.756 --> 01:21:25.757
(MEN LAUGHING)

01:21:25.840 --> 01:21:27.842
That's cool. That's all right with me.

01:21:30.053 --> 01:21:31.263
Pleasure.

01:21:36.101 --> 01:21:37.978
Oh! (VOCALIZING)

01:21:39.479 --> 01:21:41.559
- Don't do that. Stop. Stop.
- (CONTINUES VOCALIZING)

01:21:42.107 --> 01:21:43.316
- Stop that.
- Charlie.

01:21:44.025 --> 01:21:45.485
Stop it! Stop.

01:21:47.904 --> 01:21:48.989
What?

01:21:50.407 --> 01:21:51.967
Do you have any idea what you just did?

01:21:52.200 --> 01:21:53.868
Come on. We just made
the deal of our lifetimes!

01:21:53.952 --> 01:21:55.120
We should celebrate.

01:21:55.203 --> 01:21:57.122
You just bet against
the American economy.

01:21:57.205 --> 01:21:58.707
Fuck, yeah, we did!

01:21:58.790 --> 01:22:00.750
- Fuck, yeah!
- Which means...

01:22:00.834 --> 01:22:03.503
Which means if we're right...

01:22:04.546 --> 01:22:07.924
If we're right, people lose homes.
People lose jobs.

01:22:08.008 --> 01:22:11.177
People lose retirement savings.
People lose pensions.

01:22:11.303 --> 01:22:12.470
You know what I hate
about fucking banking?

01:22:12.554 --> 01:22:14.097
It reduces people to numbers.
Here's a number.

01:22:14.180 --> 01:22:17.017
Every 1% unemployment goes up,
40,000 people die. Did you know that?

01:22:17.100 --> 01:22:18.602
- No.
