- Yeah.
- But...

01:23:18.745 --> 01:23:20.625
Merrill Lynch isn't gonna
send you any customers

01:23:20.705 --> 01:23:24.250
unless you put Merrill Lynch's bonds
in your CDO.

01:23:25.377 --> 01:23:28.088
Good question. Let's just say
Merrill and I have, um...

01:23:28.713 --> 01:23:30.799
We have a good relationship.

01:23:30.924 --> 01:23:33.134
You have a good relationship
with Merrill Lynch.

01:23:33.218 --> 01:23:34.886
We've been doing business
together for a long time.

01:23:34.969 --> 01:23:37.430
And so the CDOs that you create

01:23:37.555 --> 01:23:41.476
are of the highest quality
and the highest value.

01:23:41.559 --> 01:23:43.478
- Absolutely. Yep.
- Absolutely.

01:23:43.561 --> 01:23:47.107
Are you at all concerned
about the rising default rates?

01:23:49.067 --> 01:23:52.237
I assume no risk for these
products myself, Mark.

01:23:54.906 --> 01:23:56.074
Okay.

01:23:57.659 --> 01:24:00.829
So let me get this straight.
The bank calls you up.

01:24:01.413 --> 01:24:02.956
They give you the bonds
they want to sell.

01:24:03.039 --> 01:24:04.374
They give you clients,

01:24:04.457 --> 01:24:06.835
they give you money
to run your business.

01:24:06.918 --> 01:24:08.628
Give you fat fees for doing so.

01:24:08.712 --> 01:24:10.714
But you represent the investors?

01:24:10.964 --> 01:24:11.965
(CHUCKLES)

01:24:12.257 --> 01:24:13.299
Is that right?

01:24:13.425 --> 01:24:14.467
Yeah.

01:24:14.551 --> 01:24:16.010
But we're not
in the Merrill Lynch building.

01:24:16.094 --> 01:24:17.679
- Okay. Where are you?
- We're in New Jersey.

01:24:17.762 --> 01:24:19.848
You're 20 minutes away.

01:24:19.931 --> 01:24:21.850
Well, five if you use a helicopter.

01:24:23.727 --> 01:24:24.853
That's funny, huh?

01:24:24.978 --> 01:24:26.146
That's hilarious.

01:24:26.271 --> 01:24:28.398
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:24:29.357 --> 01:24:30.400
Oh, boy.

01:24:30.775 --> 01:24:32.986
Your boss is about to explode.

01:24:33.069 --> 01:24:34.696
No, he's too curious to explode.

01:24:34.779 --> 01:24:36.239
Hold on. Say that again.

01:24:36.322 --> 01:24:38.450
CDO "A" has parts of CDO "B".

01:24:38.533 --> 01:24:40.452
And CDO "B" has parts of CDO "A".

01:24:40.535 --> 01:24:42.787
But then they both
get put inside CDO "C".

01:24:42.871 --> 01:24:44.622
Yeah, that one's called CDO squared.

01:24:44.706 --> 01:24:46.791
A CDO of a CDO.

01:24:47.208 --> 01:24:48.209
All right?

01:24:48.376 --> 01:24:50.336
And then there's CDOs
made up of the opposite side

01:24:50.420 --> 01:24:51.963
of the bet you made with your swaps.

01:24:52.213 --> 01:24:54.507
We call them synthetic CDOs.

01:24:54.632 --> 01:24:56.801
What did you say? Synthetic CDOs.

01:24:56.885 --> 01:24:58.595
That is fucking crazy.

01:24:58.720 --> 01:25:00.388
It's not. It's awesome.

01:25:01.806 --> 01:25:05.310
His face is starting to boil.
He looks like the bad guy from <i>Dune.</i>

01:25:08.188 --> 01:25:09.314
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:25:09.397 --> 01:25:11.316
All right, let's say

01:25:11.816 --> 01:25:15.153
you have a pool of $50 million
in subprime loans.

01:25:15.487 --> 01:25:18.072
How much money could be
out there betting on it,

01:25:18.156 --> 01:25:20.950
in your synthetic CDOs and swaps

01:25:21.034 --> 01:25:22.619
right now, tonight?

01:25:22.702 --> 01:25:25.330
Let's see, $50 million... Hmm...

01:25:26.331 --> 01:25:27.331
A billion dollars.

01:25:27.373 --> 01:25:28.374
What?

01:25:29.501 --> 01:25:31.419
JARED: <i>If the mortgage bonds
that Michael Burry discovered</i>

01:25:31.503 --> 01:25:32.837
<i>were the match...</i>

01:25:34.255 --> 01:25:36.674
How much bigger is the market
for insuring mortgage bonds

01:25:36.758 --> 01:25:38.218
than actual mortgages?

01:25:39.385 --> 01:25:40.553
About 20 times.

01:25:40.720 --> 01:25:42.806
JARED: <i>If the mortgage bonds
were the match</i>

01:25:42.889 --> 01:25:45.600
<i>and the CDOs were
the kerosene-soaked rags,</i>

01:25:45.683 --> 01:25:47.727
<i>then the synthetic CDO
was the atomic bomb</i>

01:25:47.811 --> 01:25:50.772
<i>with the drunk President
holding his finger over the button.</i>

01:25:50.855 --> 01:25:53.107
<i>It was at that moment
in that dumb restaurant</i>

01:25:53.191 --> 01:25:56.361
<i>with that stupid look on his face
that Mark Baum realized</i>

01:25:56.444 --> 01:25:58.863
<i>that the whole world economy
might collapse.</i>

01:26:02.492 --> 01:26:04.410
<i>And I know what you're thinking.</i>

01:26:04.494 --> 01:26:06.830
<i>"What the fuck is a synthetic CDO?"</i>

01:26:06.913 --> 01:26:07.914
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:26:09.207 --> 01:26:12.836
<i>Well, here's Dr. Richard Thaler,
father of behavioral economics</i>

01:26:12.919 --> 01:26:15.547
<i>and Selena Gomez to explain.</i>

01:26:15.880 --> 01:26:19.050
Okay. So here's how
a synthetic CDO works.

01:26:19.133 --> 01:26:22.011
Let's say I bet $10 million
on a blackjack hand.

01:26:22.095 --> 01:26:24.597
$10 million because this hand
is meant to represent

01:26:24.973 --> 01:26:27.225
a single mortgage bond.

01:26:30.186 --> 01:26:33.606
Okay, Selena has a pretty good
hand here, showing 18.

01:26:33.731 --> 01:26:34.732
Dealer showing seven.

01:26:34.816 --> 01:26:36.860
That's a really good hand for Selena.

01:26:36.943 --> 01:26:38.361
Good odds. In fact,
her chances of winning

01:26:38.444 --> 01:26:40.822
<i>this hand are 87%.</i>

01:26:40.905 --> 01:26:44.284
So, my odds are good.
I'm on a winning streak.

01:26:44.367 --> 01:26:47.036
Everybody in this place
wants to get in on the action.

01:26:47.120 --> 01:26:48.496
How could I lose, right?

01:26:48.580 --> 01:26:50.081
Now, this is a classic error.

01:26:50.164 --> 01:26:53.126
In basketball it's called
the Hot Hand Fallacy.

01:26:53.209 --> 01:26:55.753
A player makes a bunch
of shots in a row.

01:26:55.837 --> 01:26:58.131
People are sure they're
gonna make the next one.

01:26:58.214 --> 01:27:00.174
<i>People think that whatever's
happening now</i>

01:27:00.258 --> 01:27:03.011
<i>is gonna continue to
happen into the future.</i>

01:27:03.094 --> 01:27:06.431
<i>During the real estate boom,
markets were going up and up</i>

01:27:06.514 --> 01:27:08.234
and people thought
they would never go down.

01:27:08.266 --> 01:27:10.810
So people who are watching
and think that I won't lose

01:27:10.894 --> 01:27:12.353
will make a side bet.

01:27:12.437 --> 01:27:14.689
Now, this is the first synthetic CDO.

01:27:14.772 --> 01:27:16.357
I love Selena Gomez.

01:27:16.441 --> 01:27:17.942
I bet you $50 million she wins.

01:27:18.026 --> 01:27:20.111
And I'll give you 3-to-1 odds.

01:27:20.194 --> 01:27:24.032
3-to-1 odds? Okay, I'll take that bet.

01:27:24.115 --> 01:27:27.452
RICHARD: Now, somebody else
is gonna want to make a bet

01:27:27.535 --> 01:27:28.661
on the outcome of their bet.

01:27:28.828 --> 01:27:29.954
Bet you 50 million she wins.

01:27:30.038 --> 01:27:32.999
That will lead to synthetic
CDO number two.

01:27:33.082 --> 01:27:36.252
Hey, I bet you $200 million
that lady in the glasses

01:27:36.419 --> 01:27:37.921
wins that bet.

01:27:38.087 --> 01:27:41.174
She probably will win.
So I want a great payoff.

01:27:41.341 --> 01:27:42.425
How about 20-to-1?

01:27:42.550 --> 01:27:43.676
Deal.

01:27:44.010 --> 01:27:48.306
And this will go on and on with more
and more synthetic CDOs.

01:27:48.389 --> 01:27:52.435
And we can transform an original
$10 million investment

01:27:52.602 --> 01:27:54.520
into billions of dollars.

01:27:55.438 --> 01:27:56.773
You okay?

01:27:58.191 --> 01:27:59.192
